==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liken
<hw>Lik"en</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧k"'n)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Likened</conjf>
<pr>(l⟦imac⟧k"'nd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Likening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>liknen</ets>. See
<er>Like</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To allege, or
think, to be like; to represent as like; to compare; <as>as, to
<ex>liken</ex> life to a pilgrimage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whosoever heareth these sayings of mine, and doeth them, I will
<qex>liken</qex> him unto a wise man which built his house upon a
rock.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. vii. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make or cause to be like.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Brougham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Likeness</ent>⟦br⟧
